    "headings": [
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "Building communities where everyone feels safe"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "17,090,446\nPEOPLE"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "57\nRCTs"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "$2-5"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "in Colombia fall victim to crime every year"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "show the effectiveness of our approach"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "is our estimated cost to prevent one crime"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "The Problem"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "CRIME IS AN UNTREATED ENDEMIC"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "Homicides are the 3rd global cause of death for youth (15-29). In Colombia, the homicide rate is over 4× the global average."
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "CRIME IS INCREDIBLY COSTLY"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "Billions are spent on policing, prisons, and security. Crime is estimated to cost 3.12% of Colombia’s GDP, around $500 per crime."
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "CRIME IS A TOP CONCERN"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "Constant fear of crime limits how people live, work and move around. Crime is the leading worry ahead of unemployment in Latin America."
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "The Solution"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "CRIME IS PREVENTABLE"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "Existing cognitive behavioral programs have achieved long-lasting behavior changes, preventing over 300 crimes per participant over ten years at costs of less than $2 per crime."
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "OUR APPROACH IS WELL-EVIDENCED"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H1",
        "text": "57 random controlled trials (RCTs) show CBT programs can have reduction effects of 25-50% in participants."
      },
      {
        "tag": "H2",
        "text": "Meet the Team"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H2",
        "text": "An intervention endorsed by leading institutions:"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H2",
        "text": "Get in Touch"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H2",
        "text": "Be the first to get the news!"
      },
      {
        "tag": "H2",
        "text": "Sign up for our newsletter to follow us on our journey to develop the most cost-effective and scalable program against crime in Latin America."
      }
    ],
    "paragraphs": [
      "We empower at-risk youth to avoid a life of crime through Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, helping them gain control over their choices and identities.\n\nJoin us in creating safer, happier,",
      "and healthier communities.",
      "Learn more about us through:",
      "Co-Executive Director",
      "Laura Sofia Castro",
      "Colombian globetrotter with 4+ years of experience at IPA, helping over a dozen organizations design data-driven, cost-effective programs. Holds a degree in Government, Economics, and Behavioral Science from Minerva University.",
      "Co-Executive Director",
      "Henning Peters",
      "Serial non-profit entrepreneur who helped shut down a coal power plant, created an eco-village and multiple climate camps from scratch and advised over 50 grassroots groups. Psychologist with an M.Sc. and B2 level in Spanish.",
      "\"Recommended as one of our 'Best Bets' in emerging opportunities for impact at scale.\"",
      "\"Excited by the substantial positive externalities of crime reduction that we did not model.\"",
      "\"One of the most cost-effective interventions in terms of security.\"",
      "\"Targeted, short-term, and can often be delivered by non-expert facilitators.\"",
      "laura@actra.ngo",
      "henning@actra.ngo"
    ],
